---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import Card from '../../../components/Card.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Projects" description="Six projects that build toward agency-level work. The product gets harder, the process stays the same.">
  <h1 class="mb-4">Projects</h1>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">Six projects from a static website to a production system. Each follows the same <a href="/web-dev" class="text-primary hover:underline">8-step development process</a> — what changes is your role.</p>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-8">Early on, the planning is done for you. By the end, you own every step.</p>

  <!-- How your role evolves -->
  <h2 class="mb-6 mt-10">How your role evolves</h2>

  <div class="space-y-4 mb-8">
    <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <div class="text-xs font-semibold text-primary bg-primary-bg px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full">P1–P2</div>
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold">Early projects — learn the tools</h3>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Requirements, design, and architecture are provided. You focus on learning the tools and the build loop — branch, direct, verify, merge. Like being a junior on a team: someone else did the planning, you execute and verify.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <div class="text-xs font-semibold text-primary bg-primary-bg px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full">P3–P4</div>
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold">Mid projects — own the thinking</h3>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">You write the requirements yourself from a client brief. You make architecture decisions. Like a mid-level dev: you own more of the thinking, not just the execution.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <div class="text-xs font-semibold text-primary bg-primary-bg px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full">P5–P6</div>
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold">Late projects — run the agency</h3>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">You own every step. Security, multi-user systems, production ops. Like running a small agency: the client gives you a problem, you deliver a production system.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Project cards -->
  <h2 class="mb-6 mt-10 pt-8 border-t border-border">Choose a project</h2>
  <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
    <Card title="Project 1: The Static Site" subtitle="GreenScape Landscaping — a business website deployed to a real URL. 8 tickets." href="/web-dev/projects/1" />
    <Card title="Project 2: The Dynamic App" subtitle="FactFeed — database, API, Docker, CI, and automated testing. 11 tickets." href="/web-dev/projects/2" />
    <Card title="Project 3: The Interactive App" subtitle="Forms, validation, email. You plan it yourself from a client brief." />
    <Card title="Project 4: The Integrated App" subtitle="Third-party API integration (Stripe, Google Maps, or similar)." />
    <Card title="Project 5: The Multi-User App" subtitle="Auth, roles, permissions. Different users see different things." />
    <Card title="Project 6: The Live System" subtitle="Monitoring, backups, security, handover documentation." href="/web-dev/projects/6" />
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
